KAB, Antonio Bay.

463
00:42:15,489 --> 00:42:16,979
Thirty-one.

464
00:42:18,826 --> 00:42:22,785
From the top of the world,
fabulous 1340.

465
00:42:22,830 --> 00:42:29,633
The smooth sound of KAB,
Antonio Bay, California.

466
00:42:32,073 --> 00:42:34,439
Fifty-four.

467
00:42:34,475 --> 00:42:38,707
KAB 1340.

468
00:42:42,650 --> 00:42:44,982
Thirty-one.

469
00:42:45,019 --> 00:42:49,251
The sounds of the surf
from Antonio Bay.

470
00:42:49,290 --> 00:42:52,919
KAB 1340.

471
00:42:55,763 --> 00:42:57,025
Thirty-nine.

472
00:42:57,064 --> 00:43:02,934
Fabulous 1340,
KAB, Antonio Bay.

473
00:43:07,275 --> 00:43:13,111
More music on
top of the world, KAB 1340.

474
00:43:17,618 --> 00:43:22,112
EST-111-B, cut two.

475
00:43:23,791 --> 00:43:25,258
From the top of the world...

476
00:43:25,293 --> 00:43:29,730
fabulous 1340 KAB,
Antonio Bay.

477
00:43:32,433 --> 00:43:35,493
Father, where did you find this?

478
00:43:35,536 --> 00:43:39,233
My grandfather hid his sins
in the walls.

479
00:43:39,273 --> 00:43:41,741
When did you find it?

480
00:43:41,776 --> 00:43:44,904
Last night,
just after midnight.

481
00:43:44,946 --> 00:43:46,777
What difference does it make?

482
00:43:46,814 --> 00:43:49,647
That's the same time
the rest of the town fell apart.

483
00:43:54,455 --> 00:43:57,754
And the same time
the six conspirators met...

484
00:43:57,792 --> 00:44:00,192
one hundred years ago.

485
00:44:00,227 --> 00:44:02,354
It's really getting late.

486
00:44:02,396 --> 00:44:05,092
There's not much we can do
about any of this.

487
00:44:05,132 --> 00:44:08,829
Are you going to give
the benediction tonight, Father?

488
00:44:08,869 --> 00:44:12,270
Antonio Bay has a curse on it.

489
00:44:12,306 --> 00:44:14,240
Do we take that as a ''no''?

490
00:44:14,275 --> 00:44:16,470
Maybe it's just as well.

491
00:44:18,913 --> 00:44:21,882
We're leaving now, Father.

492
00:44:21,916 --> 00:44:23,941
Will you be all right?

493
00:44:26,620 --> 00:44:31,956
I'm going to call Dr. Thayden
and ask him to just drop by.

494
00:44:31,993 --> 00:44:35,019
I think you're taking
all of this much too seriously.

495
00:44:35,062 --> 00:44:38,623
We're all cursed,
Mrs. Williams...

496
00:44:38,666 --> 00:44:40,293
all of us.

497
00:44:52,513 --> 00:44:57,780
1340 KAB.

498
00:44:57,818 --> 00:45:00,048
Forty-four.

499
00:45:00,087 --> 00:45:06,993
The smooth sound.
Fabulous 1340 KAB.

500
00:45:13,267 --> 00:45:15,258
Forty-five.

501
00:45:15,302 --> 00:45:21,434
From the top of the world,
fabulous 1340 KAB...

502
00:45:21,475 --> 00:45:25,036
Antonio Bay, California.

503
00:45:25,079 --> 00:45:26,603
Forty-six.

504
00:45:27,782 --> 00:45:30,250
The smooth sound...

505
00:45:31,752 --> 00:45:35,916
Something like
an albatross around the neck...

506
00:45:35,956 --> 00:45:38,424
No. More like a millstone...

507
00:45:38,459 --> 00:45:41,257
a plumbing stone, by God.

508
00:45:41,295 --> 00:45:43,661
Damn them all!

509
00:45:59,380 --> 00:46:01,371
Nine.
Every hour on the hour...

510
00:46:01,415 --> 00:46:03,645
KAB news and weather.

511
00:46:03,684 --> 00:46:05,447
Ten.

512
00:46:05,486 --> 00:46:10,583
Every hour on the hour,
KAB news and weather.

513
00:46:12,927 --> 00:46:16,158
End side two, KAB promos.

514
00:46:26,874 --> 00:46:30,401
How can a man drown
and not touch the water?

515
00:46:30,444 --> 00:46:33,072
He had water in his lungs...

516
00:46:33,114 --> 00:46:36,845
salt water around his mouth,
seaweed in his clothes.

517
00:46:36,884 --> 00:46:38,909
Unless...

518
00:46:41,622 --> 00:46:43,681
You OK?

519
00:46:43,724 --> 00:46:46,591
Did you see his eyes?

520
00:46:46,627 --> 00:46:48,788
Yeah, I saw his eyes.

521
00:46:56,103 --> 00:46:58,936
Andy, the telephone.

522
00:46:58,973 --> 00:47:00,907
I got it, Mrs. Kobritz.

523
00:47:06,347 --> 00:47:08,212
Andy, where did you get
that piece of driftwood?

524
00:47:08,249 --> 00:47:10,843
I told you, Mom.
On the beach this morning.

525
00:47:10,885 --> 00:47:12,375
-Where?
-By the rocks.

526
00:47:12,419 --> 00:47:13,818
What was it doing?

527
00:47:13,854 --> 00:47:15,822
First it was a gold coin...

528
00:47:15,856 --> 00:47:17,949
and then it turned
into the wood.

529
00:47:17,992 --> 00:47:20,051
Andy, I want you
to stay away from the rocks.

530
00:47:20,094 --> 00:47:21,220
Do you understand?

531
00:47:21,262 --> 00:47:23,560
Don't pick up anything else
off the beach.

532
00:47:23,597 --> 00:47:25,064
It didn't belong to anybody.

533
00:47:25,099 --> 00:47:26,726
I know, honey.
It's all right.

534
00:47:26,767 --> 00:47:28,564
I just don't want you
to pick up anything else...

535
00:47:28,602 --> 00:47:30,695
unless you come
and get me first. OK?

536
00:47:30,738 --> 00:47:32,501
OK.

537
00:47:32,540 --> 00:47:34,405
Is Mrs. Kobritz there?

538
00:47:34,441 --> 00:47:36,409
She just came in.

539
00:47:36,443 --> 00:47:40,846
OK. I have to start
the broadcast now.

540
00:47:40,881 --> 00:47:43,281
Andy, promise me you won't
leave the house tonight.

541
00:47:43,317 --> 00:47:45,080
Oh, Mom.

542
00:47:45,119 --> 00:47:47,246
Promise me.

543
00:47:47,288 --> 00:47:49,654
Oh, OK.

544
00:47:49,690 --> 00:47:51,851
I love you, Andy.

545
00:47:51,892 --> 00:47:54,224
Me, too, Mom. Bye.

546
00:48:21,255 --> 00:48:22,916
Ahoy, maties.

547
00:48:22,957 --> 00:48:26,290
This is Stevie Wayne,
your night light...

548
00:48:26,327 --> 00:48:31,287
and KAB, Antonio Bay,
California, is on the air.

549
00:48:31,332 --> 00:48:33,630
I've lined up some tunes
to help you celebrate...

550
00:48:33,667 --> 00:48:36,500
the 100th birthday
of Antonio Bay.

551
00:48:36,537 --> 00:48:40,439
So let's get down to business.

552
00:49:01,795 --> 00:49:03,922
What did your mother want, Andy?

553
00:49:03,964 --> 00:49:05,363
Nothing.

554
00:49:05,399 --> 00:49:07,629
It must have been something.

555
00:49:07,668 --> 00:49:10,262
Nothing.

556
00:49:10,304 --> 00:49:13,740
Mrs. Kobritz,
what are those clouds out there?

557
00:49:20,581 --> 00:49:22,344
Evidence of deep
penetrating wounds...

558
00:49:22,383 --> 00:49:23,873
in each ocular orbit...

559
00:49:23,917 --> 00:49:26,385
entering into
the cranial cavity.

560
00:49:26,420 --> 00:49:28,945
Also jagged lacerations
to the face...

561
00:49:28,989 --> 00:49:30,650
Do you want to wait out front?

562
00:49:30,691 --> 00:49:32,556
I'd rather wait with you.

563
00:49:32,593 --> 00:49:33,958
OK.

564
00:49:33,994 --> 00:49:35,985
Thorax has been crushed...

565
00:49:36,030 --> 00:49:39,363
and the lungs
are filled with fluid.

566
00:49:39,400 --> 00:49:40,560
Talk to you a minute?

567
00:49:48,208 --> 00:49:49,903
She gonna be all right?

568
00:49:49,943 --> 00:49:52,036
-Did you talk to Simms?
-I got him on the radio.

569
00:49:52,079 --> 00:49:53,910
He's coming back
from Bodega Bay.

570
00:49:53,947 --> 00:49:55,414
What the hell
happened out there?

571
00:49:55,449 --> 00:49:57,246
There was rust
all over everything.

572
00:49:57,284 --> 00:49:58,979
It was like the boat had been
out there a long time...

573
00:49:59,019 --> 00:50:00,418
taking on water.

574
00:50:00,454 --> 00:50:02,251
He was down below
near the bunks.

575
00:50:02,289 --> 00:50:04,587
Nick, his wounds
are covered with algae...

576
00:50:04,625 --> 00:50:05,751
his lungs are full...

577
00:50:05,793 --> 00:50:07,818
and there's silt
under his fingernails.

578
00:50:07,861 --> 00:50:11,092
I saw Dick Baxter
three days ago in Salinas.

579
00:50:11,131 --> 00:50:12,496
Now he's lying in there
on the table...

580
00:50:12,533 --> 00:50:15,001
looking like he's been
underwater for a month.

581
00:50:37,491 --> 00:50:40,016
-Do you feel that?
-I'll tell you what happens.

582
00:50:40,060 --> 00:50:43,461
-It just got cold in here.
-The water acts like ice.

583
00:50:54,241 --> 00:50:56,732
A whole body would take a year
to decompose...

584
00:50:56,777 --> 00:50:59,245
longer if it was down
far enough, cold enough.

585
00:50:59,279 --> 00:51:01,076
But he was on the boat.

586
00:51:01,115 --> 00:51:02,514
He was below decks.

587
00:51:02,549 --> 00:51:06,542
No. Dick Baxter
died in the ocean.

588
00:51:22,469 --> 00:51:24,596
You remember those three kids
that went diving...

589
00:51:24,638 --> 00:51:26,970
for that old boat off the Point?

590
00:51:27,007 --> 00:51:29,100
We got to them,
they'd been down for a week...

591
00:51:29,143 --> 00:51:30,269
maybe ten days.

592
00:51:30,310 --> 00:51:34,007
I swear to you right now,
he's been down longer.

593
00:52:56,797 --> 00:52:59,163
And while the wrecking
of that beautiful ship...

594
00:52:59,199 --> 00:53:01,497
upon our coast was,
of course...

595
00:53:01,535 --> 00:53:04,561
a tragedy to those
who were on the ship...

596
00:53:04,605 --> 00:53:07,904
it still was the catalyst
that brought together...

597
00:53:07,941 --> 00:53:11,001
all of the people
of this wonderful area.

598
00:53:11,044 --> 00:53:12,443
They came together...

599
00:53:12,479 --> 00:53:15,880
they formed the charter
for Antonio Bay...

600
00:53:15,916 --> 00:53:18,976
the charter by which you have
voted for these councilmen...

601
00:53:19,019 --> 00:53:21,613
who sit on my left
and my right tonight.

602
00:53:22,856 --> 00:53:25,654
The Coast Guard's
looking for them.

603
00:53:25,692 --> 00:53:27,990
They're going to cover the area
pretty good...

604
00:53:28,028 --> 00:53:31,896
so, really,
all we can do is wait.

605
00:53:31,932 --> 00:53:34,093
I understand, Sheriff.

606
00:53:34,134 --> 00:53:35,624
Thank you.

607
00:53:37,404 --> 00:53:39,599
I got to go. I'm up next.

608
00:53:42,776 --> 00:53:45,176
I'm so sorry, Mrs. Williams.

609
00:53:48,215 --> 00:53:51,616
It's funny,
but all I can think about...

610
00:53:51,652 --> 00:53:54,883
is my silly dog
barking all night...

611
00:53:54,922 --> 00:53:59,916
and me just wishing
Al would come home.

612
00:54:02,596 --> 00:54:06,225
Now, we can't have
the chairlady...

613
00:54:06,266 --> 00:54:08,757
of the birthday celebration
in tears, can we?

614
00:54:08,802 --> 00:54:10,235
I don't think you ought
to go out there.

615
00:54:10,270 --> 00:54:14,138
I think that's exactly
what I ought to do.

616
00:54:14,174 --> 00:54:16,404
I appreciate
all your help, Nick.

617
00:54:16,443 --> 00:54:17,774
That's all right.

618
00:54:35,829 --> 00:54:38,320
I searched
a long time for this one.

619
00:54:38,365 --> 00:54:40,731
I hope you remember it.

620
00:54:45,138 --> 00:54:46,935
Happy 100th, Antonio Bay.

621
00:54:46,974 --> 00:54:50,341
The ceremonies are underway
at Shelby Square.

622
00:54:50,377 --> 00:54:53,278
And we'll have that candlelight
procession in about an hour.

623
00:54:53,313 --> 00:54:57,044
So if you hurry,
you can still make it.

624
00:54:57,084 --> 00:54:58,551
The Coast Guard
dropped me a note.

625
00:54:58,585 --> 00:55:01,645
They found the ''Sea Grass''
earlier this afternoon...

626
00:55:01,688 --> 00:55:03,178
but there's no further word...

627
00:55:03,223 --> 00:55:07,057
as to the condition of the ship
or the men on-board.

628
00:55:07,094 --> 00:55:10,427
I'll keep you posted
as the news comes in to me.

629
00:55:10,464 --> 00:55:13,297
Hope no one else gets lost
out there in the fog.

630
00:55:17,537 --> 00:55:19,095
I'll be right back.

631
00:55:28,782 --> 00:55:30,409
Hello. My name's Nick Castle.

632
00:55:30,450 --> 00:55:32,247
You don't know me,
but I'm one of the men...

633
00:55:32,285 --> 00:55:34,185
who found the ''Sea Grass''
this afternoon.

634
00:55:34,221 --> 00:55:36,519
I'm sorry.
I don't have any further word.

635
00:55:36,556 --> 00:55:38,922
I understand.
That's not what I called about.

636
00:55:38,959 --> 00:55:42,690
You just mentioned something
now on the radio about the fog.

637
00:55:51,471 --> 00:55:56,033
This is going to sound
a little strange, but...

638
00:55:56,076 --> 00:55:57,976
I saw the fog last night...

639
00:55:58,011 --> 00:55:59,535
out in the ocean
in the distance.

640
00:55:59,579 --> 00:56:02,377
It was...glowing.

641
00:56:08,522 --> 00:56:09,648
What seemed to be happening...

642
00:56:09,690 --> 00:56:11,715
is that the wind
was moving due east...

643
00:56:11,758 --> 00:56:14,056
and the fog
just kept moving west.

644
00:56:14,094 --> 00:56:15,618
I know that sounds
completely crazy.

645
00:56:15,662 --> 00:56:17,095
Right now it doesn't.

646
00:56:17,130 --> 00:56:19,291
Something happened last night.

647
00:56:19,332 --> 00:56:21,061
At the same time
that fog was moving in...

648
00:56:21,101 --> 00:56:23,092
this whole town went unglued.

649
00:56:23,136 --> 00:56:24,603
Hold on.

650
00:56:28,575 --> 00:56:31,066
I've got some more
birthday music for you...

651
00:56:31,111 --> 00:56:32,976
and a few other surprises.

652
00:56:33,013 --> 00:56:36,278
Then I'll be ready to check in
with the weatherman.

653
00:56:36,316 --> 00:56:39,774
And the weatherman will be
ready to check in with you.

654
00:56:50,597 --> 00:56:52,565
-Hello?
-I'm still here.

655
00:56:52,599 --> 00:56:53,930
There's one other thing.

656
00:56:53,967 --> 00:56:56,697
It may have nothing
to do with the ''Sea Grass''.

657
00:56:56,737 --> 00:56:58,796
Anything.

658
00:56:58,839 --> 00:57:02,570
My son found a piece
of driftwood this morning.

659
00:57:08,415 --> 00:57:11,646
Hey, Mel. How you doing?

660
00:57:11,685 --> 00:57:14,882
Your girlfriend on the radio
has been talking about you.

661
00:57:14,921 --> 00:57:16,889
I came in tonight
just to keep her happy.

662
00:57:16,923 --> 00:57:18,515
I thought
you were off tonight.

663
00:57:18,558 --> 00:57:19,718
I love my job.

664
00:57:19,760 --> 00:57:23,059
You can tell them all
about that big fog bank...

665
00:57:23,096 --> 00:57:24,757
moving in
the southeast there.

666
00:57:24,798 --> 00:57:27,392
-Where?
-You'll see it.

667
00:57:27,434 --> 00:57:29,402
I'm on my way.
See you tomorrow.

668
00:57:29,436 --> 00:57:31,427
Yeah, Mel. I'll see you.

669
00:57:41,314 --> 00:57:42,838
There you are.

670
00:57:52,859 --> 00:57:54,451
I've got to make a run
out to the lighthouse...

671
00:57:54,494 --> 00:57:56,018
at Spivey Point.
Want to come?

672
00:57:56,062 --> 00:57:57,324
-Sure.
-Come on.

673
00:58:03,069 --> 00:58:04,468
Hi, sweetheart!

674
00:58:04,504 --> 00:58:05,732
I thought you were celebrating.

675
00:58:05,772 --> 00:58:08,570
I couldn't spend an evening
without you.

676
00:58:08,608 --> 00:58:11,270
I'm up in about thirty seconds.
What's new?

677
00:58:11,311 --> 00:58:13,472
Another fog bank.

678
00:58:13,513 --> 00:58:14,946
Where?

679
00:58:14,981 --> 00:58:17,245
It's coming in off the ocean
from the southeast.

680
00:58:17,284 --> 00:58:19,047
It's heading inland.
It should be here...

681
00:58:19,085 --> 00:58:20,780
at the weather station
in ten minutes.

682
00:58:20,821 --> 00:58:23,381
Dan, hold on.

683
00:58:24,724 --> 00:58:26,783
I have a special
weather bulletin.

684
00:58:26,827 --> 00:58:28,385
The tri-county
weather station...

685
00:58:28,428 --> 00:58:31,795
reports a fog bank moving
southeast along the coast.

686
00:58:31,832 --> 00:58:33,527
For whoever's interested...

687
00:58:33,567 --> 00:58:36,900
that's the weather station
on Old Russellville Road.

688
00:58:36,937 --> 00:58:40,930
Repeating--a fog bank is moving
southwest along the coast...

689
00:58:40,974 --> 00:58:44,102
toward the weather station
on Old Russellville Road.

690
00:58:48,915 --> 00:58:50,746
Dan, are you still there?

691
00:58:50,784 --> 00:58:53,082
I'm still here.

692
00:58:53,119 --> 00:58:55,144
You sound different tonight...

693
00:58:55,188 --> 00:58:57,213
kind of intense.

694
00:58:57,257 --> 00:58:59,885
I just feel like talking,
that's all.

695
00:58:59,926 --> 00:59:02,224
You told me you didn't like
to talk on the telephone...

696
00:59:02,262 --> 00:59:04,059
because you talked
on the radio all day.

697
00:59:04,097 --> 00:59:05,291
Dan, where's the fog now?

698
00:59:05,332 --> 00:59:08,233
It should be
right outside my door now.

699
00:59:11,404 --> 00:59:13,201
Hold on.
I'm going to try something.

700
00:59:18,778 --> 00:59:19,972
I can see it.

701
00:59:20,013 --> 00:59:22,743
Now, what is the big deal?

702
00:59:22,782 --> 00:59:24,841
You've seen fog once,
you seen it for life.

703
00:59:24,885 --> 00:59:26,910
There's something
different about this fog.

704
00:59:26,953 --> 00:59:29,751
It glows.
Can't you see anything yet?

705
00:59:29,789 --> 00:59:33,247
Glows? Oh, I get it.

706
00:59:33,293 --> 00:59:35,261
You take something
to keep you going, right?

707
00:59:35,295 --> 00:59:37,957
Does it make you feel
a little weird sometimes?

708
00:59:39,132 --> 00:59:41,930
-Hey.
-What?

709
00:59:41,968 --> 00:59:43,936
The lights went out.

710
00:59:43,970 --> 00:59:47,269
Everything's going crazy.

711
00:59:47,307 --> 00:59:49,707
Barometer's falling,
temperature's dropping.

712
00:59:49,743 --> 00:59:51,711
Dan, what is it?

713
00:59:51,745 --> 00:59:53,144
What the hell's that?

714
00:59:53,179 --> 00:59:54,874
Dan, what is it?
What's happening?

715
00:59:54,915 --> 00:59:57,383
What is it?
What's happening?

716
00:59:57,417 --> 00:59:59,885
Someone's shining a light
through the window.

717
00:59:59,920 --> 01:00:01,217
Dan, listen to me.

718
01:00:01,254 --> 01:00:04,087
Hold on, sweetheart.
I want to check this out.

719
01:00:06,927 --> 01:00:10,055
Dan, stay on the phone!

720
01:00:21,508 --> 01:00:23,408
This has got to be a joke.

721
01:00:28,381 --> 01:00:30,906
Someone's at the front door,
sweetheart...

722
01:00:30,951 --> 01:00:32,816
playing a stupid joke.

723
01:00:32,852 --> 01:00:35,548
And whoever it is...

724
01:00:35,588 --> 01:00:37,886
they ain't gonna like
finding me home.

725
01:00:37,924 --> 01:00:39,721
Dan, stay away from the door!

726
01:00:56,609 --> 01:00:57,906
Anybody here?

727
01:01:01,414 --> 01:01:03,712
Some asshole got drunk
and started taking...

728
01:01:03,750 --> 01:01:06,514
this 100-year-old business
too seriously.

729
01:01:59,472 --> 01:02:03,533
And so all of us living here
in Antonio Bay today...

730
01:02:03,576 --> 01:02:05,703
owe a great debt
of gratitude...

731
01:02:05,745 --> 01:02:08,179
to those men and women
a hundred years ago...

732
01:02:08,214 --> 01:02:11,377
who struggled and sacrificed
to make this town grow...

733
01:02:11,418 --> 01:02:13,113
into what it is today.

734
01:02:13,153 --> 01:02:17,613
And it's up to us to keep
their kind of spirit alive.

735
01:02:22,595 --> 01:02:23,823
I have an urgent bulletin.

736
01:02:23,863 --> 01:02:27,594
Will Sheriff David Simms please
contact KAB Radio immediately?

737
01:02:27,634 --> 01:02:30,694
The number is 555-2131.

738
01:02:30,737 --> 01:02:32,466
This is an emergency.

739
01:02:34,641 --> 01:02:38,975
So we must redouble our efforts,
work together.

740
01:02:39,012 --> 01:02:41,537
We have a vital,
thriving community.

741
01:02:41,581 --> 01:02:44,049
And I say
we have to keep it that way.

742
01:02:47,187 --> 01:02:49,121
This is an emergency.

743
01:02:49,155 --> 01:02:52,613
Sheriff David Simms,
please contact KAB immediately.

744
01:02:52,659 --> 01:02:56,390
555-2131.
This is an emergency.

745
01:03:11,544 --> 01:03:12,738
Sheriff Simms?

746
01:03:18,718 --> 01:03:20,549
And so, as we make our way...

747
01:03:20,587 --> 01:03:22,248
to the presentation
of the statue...

748
01:03:22,288 --> 01:03:24,586
I think we should all
keep in mind...

749
01:03:24,624 --> 01:03:26,216
the significance
of this night...

750
01:03:26,259 --> 01:03:28,591
for every citizen
of Antonio Bay.

751
01:04:16,809 --> 01:04:20,575
We should all proceed
over to the statue.

752
01:04:20,613 --> 01:04:22,672
Single file. Don't push.

753
01:04:22,715 --> 01:04:24,307
Take your time.

754
01:04:50,543 --> 01:04:52,511
Start!

755
01:04:52,545 --> 01:04:54,536
Please start!

756
01:04:58,918 --> 01:05:00,681
Why did all the lights go out?

757
01:05:00,720 --> 01:05:05,657
One of the lines
are probably down, Andy.

758
01:05:05,692 --> 01:05:09,389
They usually take care
of these things right away.

759
01:05:09,429 --> 01:05:12,125
I think it's kind of neat.

760
01:05:39,425 --> 01:05:41,290
What's that now?

761
01:05:57,844 --> 01:05:59,368
Start!

762
01:06:05,118 --> 01:06:07,518
Andy! Andy,
get out of the house!

763
01:06:07,553 --> 01:06:09,885
Mrs. Kobritz, get him
out of the house! Please! Run!

764
01:06:09,922 --> 01:06:12,857
I think maybe we better
close all the windows, Andy.

765
01:06:12,892 --> 01:06:14,587
Are your bedroom windows
closed?

766
01:06:14,627 --> 01:06:15,889
I'll go see.

767
01:06:24,771 --> 01:06:27,205
Someone listen to me!
My son is trapped!

768
01:06:27,240 --> 01:06:30,209
887 White Beach Lane!
My son is trapped by the fog!

769
01:06:30,243 --> 01:06:32,541
Andy, get out of the house!
Run!

770
01:06:37,083 --> 01:06:40,109
Wow! Look at that!

771
01:06:40,153 --> 01:06:41,916
Are your windows all closed?

772
01:06:41,954 --> 01:06:43,285
Yes, ma'am.

773
01:06:43,323 --> 01:06:44,881
What about
your mother's bedroom?

774
01:06:56,636 --> 01:06:59,696
Please, someone!
My son is trapped!

775
01:07:02,275 --> 01:07:04,175
Andy, run! Run!

776
01:07:04,210 --> 01:07:06,474
Mrs. Kobritz, run!

777
01:07:09,515 --> 01:07:12,313
Andy, I want you
to go to your room.

778
01:07:12,352 --> 01:07:13,910
I think I should stay.

779
01:07:13,953 --> 01:07:16,319
-Right now.
-Yes.

780
01:07:37,377 --> 01:07:38,605
Go to your room.

781
01:07:38,644 --> 01:07:40,305
I want to see who it is.

782
01:07:41,714 --> 01:07:43,739
Can't I stay
for two more seconds?

783
01:07:46,719 --> 01:07:49,347
OK, I'm going.

784
01:08:03,202 --> 01:08:05,193
Mrs. Kobritz?

785
01:08:15,248 --> 01:08:17,580
Please. My son is trapped!

786
01:08:17,617 --> 01:08:21,519
887 White Beach Lane.

787
01:08:21,554 --> 01:08:24,148
Someone get
to 887 White Beach Lane.

788
01:08:36,903 --> 01:08:40,703
My son is trapped!
Get him out of the fog!

789
01:08:47,413 --> 01:08:49,404
Please, someone!

790
01:08:50,683 --> 01:08:52,241
My son is trapped!

791
01:09:01,194 --> 01:09:03,094
Come on!
Get out of there, now!

792
01:09:11,971 --> 01:09:14,667
Andy, run! Run!

793
01:09:17,276 --> 01:09:19,141
Come on! Come on.

794
01:09:19,178 --> 01:09:20,941
Go! Go!

795
01:09:33,226 --> 01:09:34,488
Come on!

796
01:09:34,527 --> 01:09:37,792
Don't pop it.
Try to ease it out.

797
01:09:37,830 --> 01:09:39,388
Oh, Jesus.

798
01:09:45,471 --> 01:09:47,029
Come on, baby!

799
01:09:47,073 --> 01:09:50,531
Come on. It'll go.

800
01:09:50,576 --> 01:09:51,736
Reverse! Reverse!

801
01:09:51,777 --> 01:09:53,210
Come on!

802
01:10:00,253 --> 01:10:02,118
Come on, do it! Do it!

803
01:10:27,079 --> 01:10:29,104
...Stevie Wayne
for the last twenty minutes.

804
01:10:29,315 --> 01:10:31,579
I think it's best
we call it a night here.

805
01:10:31,617 --> 01:10:33,084
Another five or ten minutes...

806
01:10:33,119 --> 01:10:34,916
everyone will have
seen the statue.

807
01:10:34,954 --> 01:10:37,422
All right, but let's get them
through as quickly as we can.

808
01:10:37,456 --> 01:10:39,924
Probably be a good idea
if you went home, Kathy.

809
01:10:39,959 --> 01:10:41,586
We can close up here.

810
01:10:41,627 --> 01:10:42,924
I should see it through
to the end.

811
01:10:42,962 --> 01:10:45,260
Mrs. Williams,
there's nothing more to do here.

812
01:10:45,298 --> 01:10:47,664
Let me take you home.

813
01:10:47,700 --> 01:10:50,533
A little annoying,
but you're right.

814
01:10:50,570 --> 01:10:52,697
-Would you please take me?
-Yes, ma'am.

815
01:10:52,738 --> 01:10:55,400
-I'll call you tomorrow.
-Thank you.

816
01:11:00,146 --> 01:11:02,512
Andy, I don't even know
if you can hear me.

817
01:11:02,548 --> 01:11:04,641
I'm sorry that
I didn't come for you...

818
01:11:04,684 --> 01:11:05,844
that I wasn't there.

819
01:11:07,253 --> 01:11:09,744
Andy, please understand.

820
01:11:11,591 --> 01:11:14,424
I have to stay here.

821
01:11:25,371 --> 01:11:29,637
The fog is moving inland...

822
01:11:29,675 --> 01:11:31,575
away from the beach...

823
01:11:34,180 --> 01:11:36,114
towards Antonio Bay.

824
01:11:42,088 --> 01:11:44,249
It's over by the armory.

825
01:11:44,290 --> 01:11:47,020
I can't remember the name.

826
01:11:47,059 --> 01:11:49,857
No, no--
I think it's Chestnut.

827
01:11:54,634 --> 01:11:57,694
Feel like listening
to some music?

828
01:11:57,737 --> 01:12:00,228
Sure.

829
01:12:00,272 --> 01:12:02,137
It's moving faster now.

830
01:12:02,174 --> 01:12:03,664
Up Regent Avenue.

831
01:12:03,709 --> 01:12:05,700
Up to the end
of Smallhouse Road.

832
01:12:05,745 --> 01:12:07,178
What is that?

833
01:12:09,882 --> 01:12:12,442
It's just hitting
the outskirts of town.

834
01:12:12,485 --> 01:12:14,476
Broad Street.

835
01:12:15,921 --> 01:12:18,412
Clay Street.

836
01:12:44,784 --> 01:12:46,615
It's moving down 10th Street.

837
01:12:46,652 --> 01:12:50,110
Get inside and lock your doors.
Close your windows.

838
01:12:50,156 --> 01:12:52,386
There's something in the fog.

839
01:12:58,964 --> 01:13:01,296
If you're on the south side
of town, go north.

840
01:13:01,333 --> 01:13:03,301
Stay away from the fog.

841
01:13:11,711 --> 01:13:13,804
Richardsville Pike
up to Beacon Hill...

842
01:13:13,846 --> 01:13:16,212
is the only clear road.

843
01:13:16,248 --> 01:13:18,216
Up to the church.

844
01:13:18,250 --> 01:13:21,344
If you can get out of town,
get to the old church.

845
01:13:29,195 --> 01:13:31,629
Now the junction at 101
is cut off.

846
01:13:31,664 --> 01:13:35,122
If you can get out of town,
get to the old church.

847
01:13:35,167 --> 01:13:37,067
It's the only place
left to go.

848
01:13:37,103 --> 01:13:39,936
Get to the old church
on Beacon Hill.

849
01:13:48,114 --> 01:13:49,911
-It cut us off!
-Where is it?

850
01:13:49,949 --> 01:13:51,678
-Right behind us.
-Quick, inside.

851
01:13:55,154 --> 01:13:56,849
Come on.

852
01:13:56,889 --> 01:13:58,049
Hurry.

853
01:13:59,925 --> 01:14:02,860
Father, is there a basement
or cellar in here?

854
01:14:02,895 --> 01:14:04,920
-We can't hide any longer.
-We have to try!

855
01:14:04,964 --> 01:14:06,898
No matter where we go,
it will find us.

856
01:14:11,337 --> 01:14:13,032
Is there a basement
or cellar here?

857
01:14:13,072 --> 01:14:15,040
There's a study in back.
I'll show you the way.

858
01:14:15,074 --> 01:14:16,507
Come on. Hurry.

859
01:14:16,542 --> 01:14:18,908
Give me that.

860
01:14:47,973 --> 01:14:49,907
The fog is sweeping inland.

861
01:14:51,410 --> 01:14:54,243
It's almost like a wall
across the east end of town.

862
01:15:18,838 --> 01:15:20,703
Blake and his men
have come for us.

863
01:15:20,739 --> 01:15:22,331
-Who's Blake?
-It's in the journal.

864
01:15:22,374 --> 01:15:23,500
-What journal?
-I don't know.

865
01:15:23,542 --> 01:15:25,840
-We're cursed.
-What are you talking about?

866
01:15:25,878 --> 01:15:29,075
-Where is the journal?
-It's in there.

867
01:15:35,154 --> 01:15:36,485
Over by the window?

868
01:15:36,522 --> 01:15:39,548
-It can do us no good now.
-It's all we got.

869
01:15:39,592 --> 01:15:41,287
If anything happens,
just lock the door.

870
01:15:41,327 --> 01:15:43,659
Get back. Shut the door.

871
01:16:23,903 --> 01:16:25,097
''Six must die.''

872
01:16:25,137 --> 01:16:26,399
The three men
on the ''Sea Grass''.

873
01:16:26,438 --> 01:16:28,030
And the weatherman is four.

874
01:16:28,073 --> 01:16:29,540
-Mrs. Kobritz.
-Yeah, five.

875
01:16:29,575 --> 01:16:31,042
And one of us makes six.

876
01:16:31,076 --> 01:16:32,703
That's what they want.
They've come back...

877
01:16:32,745 --> 01:16:34,372
for the six
original conspirators.

878
01:16:34,413 --> 01:16:35,846
There must be something
in here!

879
01:16:35,881 --> 01:16:37,371
It's me they want.
I am the sixth!

880
01:16:37,416 --> 01:16:38,542
Why would they want you?

881
01:16:38,584 --> 01:16:39,881
Wait, Father.
You didn't read us this.

882
01:16:39,919 --> 01:16:41,887
''Were it possible
to raise the dead...

883
01:16:41,921 --> 01:16:44,219
''I would return Blake's fortune
to him intact...

884
01:16:44,256 --> 01:16:47,191
''save the money spent
on these walls that hide it.''

885
01:16:47,226 --> 01:16:49,126
''My fellow conspirators
believe...

886
01:16:49,161 --> 01:16:51,152
''that the confiscated fortune
has been stolen...

887
01:16:51,196 --> 01:16:53,824
''from them, when in fact,
I am the thief...

888
01:16:53,866 --> 01:16:56,334
''and God's temple
is the tomb of gold.''

889
01:16:56,368 --> 01:16:59,895
''I am the thief,
and God's temple--''

890
01:17:01,774 --> 01:17:03,969
Now, wait. Get rid of that.

891
01:17:05,577 --> 01:17:08,137
Get out of the way!

892
01:17:29,268 --> 01:17:32,704
-Give me a hand.
-Andy, stay right there.

893
01:17:56,395 --> 01:17:58,090
The gold.

894
01:18:17,016 --> 01:18:19,314
He melted down the gold
into this.

895
01:18:23,389 --> 01:18:25,254
Somebody help her!

896
01:18:38,404 --> 01:18:40,167
Don't go in there!

897
01:19:21,080 --> 01:19:23,947
Blake, I have your gold.

898
01:19:31,356 --> 01:19:32,516
Blake?

899
01:20:10,596 --> 01:20:12,530
This is your gold, Blake.

900
01:20:12,564 --> 01:20:15,931
My grandfather stole it
from you.

901
01:20:17,970 --> 01:20:20,768
I'm the one
who must answer for it.

902
01:20:33,452 --> 01:20:36,444
I'm the sixth conspirator.

903
01:20:38,457 --> 01:20:41,585
I'm Father Malone.

904
01:20:41,627 --> 01:20:43,788
Take me.

905
01:21:40,152 --> 01:21:41,949
Father Malone!

906
01:24:01,626 --> 01:24:02,991
Look.

907
01:24:13,238 --> 01:24:14,899
It's going away.

908
01:24:50,876 --> 01:24:54,312
I don't know what happened
to Antonio Bay tonight.

909
01:24:54,346 --> 01:24:57,679
Something came out of the fog...

910
01:24:57,716 --> 01:25:00,617
and tried to destroy us.

911
01:25:00,652 --> 01:25:03,678
In one moment, it vanished.

912
01:25:03,722 --> 01:25:07,214
But if this has been
anything but a nightmare...

913
01:25:07,259 --> 01:25:11,127
and if we don't wake up to find
ourselves safe in our beds...

914
01:25:11,163 --> 01:25:14,929
it could come again.

915
01:25:14,966 --> 01:25:18,402
To the ships at sea
who can hear my voice...

916
01:25:18,437 --> 01:25:22,669
look across the water
into the darkness.

917
01:25:24,075 --> 01:25:26,236
Look for the fog.

918
01:25:54,739 --> 01:25:57,867
Why not six, Blake?

919
01:26:00,378 --> 01:26:02,471
Why not me?

